<content type="str">Bobby Jack Horn, 87, of Ozark went to be with his Lord and Savior on Friday, Jan. 27, 2017. He was a member of Faith Pentecostal Church of God in Ozark. Bob was a proud Korean War veteran and retired plant manager for Cargill Inc. Bob was born Dec. 14, 1929, in Denning to Chester “Red” Horn and Gussie Taylor Horn. He was preceded in death by his parents and his wife of 62 years, Wanda Walker Horn. 
 
He is survived by his daughter, Linda Hufford; and his son, Don Horn and wife Glenda, both of Ozark; a granddaughter, Bridget Langston and husband Paul; and two great-grandchildren, Lindsey and Haeven Langston of Fort Smith. 
 
Graveside service will be held at 10 a.m. Tuesday at Cemetery Ridge Cemetery with Brother James Jones officiating under the direction of Shaffer Funeral Home in Ozark. 
 
Pallbearers serving are Paul Langston, Haeven Langston, Garrett Tinsley, J.L. Wade, Kenneth Nichols and Doyle “Spider” Bowman. 
 
The family will visit with friends from 6-8 p.m. Monday at Shaffer Funeral Home, 2315 West Commercial Street in Ozark. 
 
Please visit the website shafferfuneralhomeweb.com to leave an online condolence.</content> 
